\end{proof}

We give an example showing that our approach does not work for the connected component $G$ of the even orthogonal similitude group $GO_{2l}$. Let $l = 4$ and choose $p, r$ such that $4 \vert p^r - 1$. Let $T, T', d$ be as in \ref{cor: simple polynomial GrT-modules for GL_n, GSp_2l, GO2_l+1}.(b). Let  $\varphi: X(T') \rightarrow {\mathbb{Z}}$, $t \mapsto \sum_{i=1}^l \min \{t_i, t_{i'} \}$. The same proof shows that with the exception of $(iv)$, all statements in the proof of \ref{thm: construction of phi} hold for $\varphi$ and $d$. Let $\lambda_0, \tilde{\lambda} \in X(T')$ be the characters given by $\lambda_0 =(\frac{p^r - 1}{2}, \frac{p^r - 1}{2}, \frac{p^r - 1}{2}, \frac{p^r - 1}{2}, \frac{p^r - 1}{4}, \frac{p^r - 1}{4}, \frac{p^r - 1}{4}, \frac{p^r - 1}{4})$ and $\tilde{\lambda} = (0,0,0,0, 1, 1, -1, 1)$. Then $\varphi(\lambda_0) = p^r - 1 > 0$, $\varphi(\lambda_0 - p^r d) = -1 < 0$ and $\lambda_0 \vert_{T} \in X_r(T)$, so that $\lambda_{0} \vert_{T} \in P_r(D)$. In $W \cong S_l \ltimes ({\mathbb{Z}}/(2))^{l-1}$, $S_l$ acts on $X(T')$ as in the proof of \ref{cor: simple polynomial GrT-modules for GL_n, GSp_2l, GO2_l+1}.(b) while $({\mathbb{Z}}/(2))^{l-1}$ acts as the subgroup $\lbrace x \in ({\mathbb{Z}}/(2))^l \vert x_i \neq 0$ for an even number of $i \rbrace$ of $({\mathbb{Z}}/(2))^{l}$. Thus, $\lambda_0$ is invariant under $S_l$ and we have $\varphi(w. \lambda_0 \vert_{T} + p^r \tilde{\lambda} \vert_{T}) > 0$ and hence $w. \lambda_0 \vert_{T} + p^r \tilde{\lambda}\vert_{T} \in X(D)$ for all $w \in ({\mathbb{Z}}/(2))^{l-1}$. Hence the arguments in the proof of \ref{thm: all weights of simple modules polynomial iff weight belongs to Xr(D)+p^r P(D)} are not applicable in this case. As the statement $w. \lambda_0 \vert_T + p^r \tilde{\lambda} \vert_T \in X(D)$ does not depend on $\varphi$ and there is no other choice for $d$ in this case, we cannot find other $\varphi$ or $d$ in this example to salvage the proof of \ref{thm: all weights of simple modules polyn